[139.851277, "o", "                                                                                                                                                                                \r\n\u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[38;2;62;71;77m\u001b[48;2;232;220;198m  \u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[38;2;185;192;171m\u001b[48;2;232;220;198m 10 \u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[38;2;62;71;77m\u001b[48;2;232;220;198mThe new pitch is structurally a near-clone of Voyager Digital's core business: accept US consumer deposits in crypto (stablecoins, BTC), custody them, and generate yield by deploying c\u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[38;2;62;71;77m\u001b[48;2;232;220;198m  \u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[38;2;185;192;171m\u001b[48;2;232;220;198m    \u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[38;2;62;71;77m\u001b[48;2;232;220;198mapital to institutional borrowers and market makers. Both use a tiered interest/lock-up model, both target retail users via web and mobile, both rely on institutional counterparty rela\u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[38;2;62;71;77m\u001b[48;2;232;220;198m  \u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[38;2;185;192;171m\u001b[48;2;232;220;198m    \u001b(B\u001b[m\u001b[38;2;62;71;77m\u001b[48;2;232;220;198mtionships to fund the yield promise, and both operate in the same US regulatory en"]
[139.851326, "o", "vironment that ultimately scrutinized Voyager for misleading FDIC/banking insurance claims.           \u001b[19;7H\u001b[?2026l"]
